Package com.github.dkanellis.fikey.storage

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Initializable
    An initializable object must be initialized before used.
    U2fDeviceStorage
    An interface which declares the functionality of a U2F compatible device storage.
    U2fRequestStorage
    An interface which declares the functionality of a storage which will store and pop all the requests from U2F devices.
    U2fUser
    A U2fUser should be able to take care of the first part of the two-factor authentication by being able to recognize if the password given is correct and should also be able to return the username.
    U2fUserStorage
    An interface which declares the functionality of a user storage.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Devices
    Holds all the devices in the website/application using Google's LoadingCache.
    Requests
    In this U2fRequestStorage implementation a HashMap is used to store each request's id and information stored in Json format.
    User
    A simple representation of a website/application FIDO user.
    Users
    A U2fUserStorage implementation with a Set as it's backbone to ensure unique users and great search performance.
